rd deftly capture the poet’s unmistakable voice—cool and precise, gently ironic, and deeply humane.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aHolocaust.  awar.1 aBogoczek, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoward, Tony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012z978311127413308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2012z978311127716540uhttps://doi.org/10.15215/aupress/9781927356029.0140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781927356036423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781927356036/original  a978-3-11-127413-3  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012b2012  a978-3-11-127716-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2012b2012  aGBV-deGruyter-alles